<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-11-05T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-11-05T03:00:00-05:00" n="232" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d232">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/5581: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Tenney</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-11-05T16:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">November 5,
                                        1919, 4 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received November 6, 7:45
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>[From <persName corresp="#p_HEL1">Harris</persName> at Omsk:]</p>
                        <p>457. <persName corresp="#p_DGMK1">General Dietrichs</persName> has
                            resigned as commander of Siberian Army and has been succeeded by General
                            Sakharoff. <persName corresp="#p_KGVO1">General Kappel</persName> has
                            been placed in charge of third army.</p>
                        <p>Weather has turned extremely cold. To-day thermometer registers 15° below
                            zero Reaumur. Since occupation of Petropavlovsk by Bolsheviki
                            practically no change in military operations. Preparations for
                            evacuation of Omsk by diplomatic and military missions now actively
                            progressing.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tenney</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>